[Humboldt County is on the northern border of Nevada with Oregon: see http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/united_states/nevada_90.jpg and http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/united_states/united_states_pol02.jpg. A more detailed map of the shooting area is in the report itself.

In winter the bighorn sheep herds will be restricted to their individually preferred winter grazing areas. But come the spring thaw they will move out. And this disease is becoming more serious with each year, indicating a measure of inter-herd contacts, exchange of _Mycoplasma ovipneumoniae_ followed by a polymicrobial pneumonia; see 20160109.3923355. It will be interesting to see how effective this area slaughter is. Obviously if we had an effective vaccine and an efficient mode of delivery, the control would be more effective and acceptable. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4033226,230.]
